For full context read [docs/ai-guide.md](../../docs/ai-guide.md).

## Non-negotiable rules

- **Always import `z` from `../../../shared/lib/zod`**, never directly from `'zod'`
- **Errors:** throw `AppError(message, statusCode)` — never `res.status(x).json(...)` directly in error paths
- **Responses:** always wrap in `{ status: 'success', data }` or `res.status(204).send()`
- **Validation:** use `validate(ZodSchema)` middleware — never validate manually in controllers
- **Auth:** protect routes with `authMiddleware` from `shared/middleware/auth.middleware`
- **SQL:** parameterized queries only (`$1`, `$2`…), never string interpolation

## Module structure

```
src/modules/<feature>/
  dtos/               ← Zod schemas + inferred types
  repositories/       ← SQL only, no business logic
  services/           ← business logic, throws AppError
  controllers/        ← req/res only, delegates to service
  <feature>.routes.ts
  <feature>.swagger.ts
```

## Registering a new module

1. `src/app.ts` → `app.use('/api/<feature>', featureRoutes)`
2. `src/shared/swagger/swagger.config.ts` → add side-effect import of `<feature>.swagger`
3. `docker/postgres/init.sql` → add new tables
